    "line": 189,
    "summary": "compactTrailing always uses countRateLevel.color regardless of which radiation type is active",
    "failure_scenario": "The ternary selects the value to display based on activeRadiationType (countRate vs doseRate), but the foreground color is hard-coded to `context.state.countRateLevel.color`. When activeRadiationType == .doseRate, the label shows the doseRate value in the countRate level's color (e.g. green when count rate is normal but dose rate is at level2/yellow). The old code had the same issue with the String value; the new Float? version preserves it."
  }
